article.headline: Winthrop 75, Liberty 73 (OT)
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) --Phillip Williams and Otis Daniels scored 17 points each to lead Winthrop to a 75-73 overtime win over Liberty on Saturday night. Daniels' layup with 24 seconds left in overtime was enough for the Eagles (10-5, 1-1 Big South Conference), who held on for the victory. The Flames (2-11, 0-2) scored on the opening possession of overtime, but Winthrop tied the game at 73, then Williams blocked back-to-back shots. Williams forced overtime by making one of two free throws with 23 seconds remaining to tie the game at 66. Liberty had taken a 66-65 lead with 53 second left when David Dees, who had 27 points and five rebounds, hit a 3. Larry Blair added 23 points for Liberty. Winthrop took a 21-6 lead in the opening nine minutes of play before Liberty went on a 14-0 run to get within one at 21-20 with 6:53 left in the first half. But the Eagles scored and took a 32-31 halftime lead.
